00:02:16.299 --> 00:02:21.040
For example, pigeon navigation isn't well
understood, but a 2013 paper in the Journal

00:02:21.040 --> 00:02:26.480
of Experimental Biology posits it has to do
with infrasound, or extreme low frequency

00:02:26.480 --> 00:02:30.349
sound waves generated by the ocean and reverberating
through our planet.

00:02:30.349 --> 00:02:34.939
Using these pervasive sounds, the researchers
believe, pigeons can make a mental map of

00:02:34.939 --> 00:02:37.109
their surroundings and find their way home.

00:02:37.109 --> 00:02:40.809
And, this month, a new study in the Proceedings
of the National Academy of Sciences explored

00:02:40.809 --> 00:02:45.650
this superbird, finding their flying is some
of the best in the bird world.

00:02:45.650 --> 00:02:49.760
They can avoid cars and predators and when
captured with high speed cameras they found

00:02:49.760 --> 00:02:54.419
the simple pigeon could hold their wings up
to slide through small spaces; OR they can

00:02:54.419 --> 00:02:59.469
tuck them in to barrel through holes and protect
their body in case of miscalculation.

00:02:59.469 --> 00:03:04.290
